when a tom cat reaches puberty does his voice break yesterday my month old tom cat's miouw suddenly deepened into a growl and he is still growling instead of mewing today he isnt in a bad mood has his voice broken or is he just hoarse or does he have a sore throat or something he's had all his vaccinations and is eating well so i dont think he's caught any virus could it mean he has a fur ball in his throat martin yes he is stripey but he assures me he is a tabby not a tiger male cats do have a deeper growly call when they're in the mood for love even female cats can have a startling raucous cry when in season especially siamese if your cat is eating and drinking normally i don't think you need to worry but bear in mind that there are lots of good reasons to have tomcats neutered as you will realise if he scent marks your house Cat Team Rocket Ferret Maine Coon Shaggy dog story Tiger Kakapo Tabby cat Castration The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Fancy rat Taboo food and drink The Invisibles Cheetah Pet skunk Singlish Cats (musical) Dog Domestic rabbit The Shining (film) Gray Wolf Tortoiseshell cat Tom and Jerry (MGM) Trailer Park Boys Gollum Cat coat genetics Turkish Van Hyakujuu Sentai GaoRanger Ty Cobb Rent (musical) Bengal cat Dog training Influenza The Wizard of Oz (1939 film) The Fairly OddParents Parsifal The Marshall Mathers LP Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Relative clause One Piece minor characters Common cold Feral cat Timon and Pumbaa Animal communication Cocaine The Unquiet Dead Ginny Weasley House of Leaves Pitaten Conker's Bad Fur Day Babe Ruth Virus English grammar Asiatic Golden Cat Ron and Fez New York Giants The Beach Boys RuneScape quests Atomic Kitten Time Out of Mind Pharyngitis Giovanni (Pok__mon) EastEnders Rocko's Modern Life Death grunt Ebola Kitten Southeast Asia John the Baptist Pep__ Le Pew Chronic fatigue syndrome H5N1 Leopard Shrek 2 Babe Ruth's Called Shot Academy Award for Directing Bulgarian language Siamese (cat) Re